### L2 — Resume: HTTP 202 when a suspended session is found
### SPEC §6.3 and §7.4
### The session was created on a desktop browser, which then closed.
### The user opens the app on their phone and sends a message.
### The server finds the suspended session and returns HTTP 202 instead of
### processing the request — giving the client a chance to offer a resume.

POST /v1/chat/completions HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your-api-key>

{
  "model": "claude-opus-4-7",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the capital of France?" }
  ],
  "sbp": {
    "force_new_session": false
  }
}

### Response — HTTP 202 Resume Available
### The model field can be any model — switching from gpt-4o to claude-opus-4-7
### mid-session is valid. Sessions are model-agnostic.

HTTP/1.1 202 Accepted
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sbp": {
    "session_id":       "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "snapshot_id":      "b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901",
    "resume_available": true,
    "resume_prompt":    "You were last working on: planning a 3-day trip to Tokyo. You completed step 12.",
    "last_checkpoint":  "2026-05-10T15:00:00Z",
    "step_count":       12
  }
}

### To resume, the client resends with force_new_session: false (default).
### The server picks up the suspended session and continues from the snapshot.
